            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "As someone who maintains and contributes to lots of plugins, reducing friction here is high value to me. It's also a common feature in many (all?) third party managers and isn't complex to support.\n\nMy current manager simply detects if source is a local path, and if it is it just symlinks the dir into `opt` instead of `git clone`, then update operations work as normal.\n\nIf I can't have this supported then I simply won't use `vim.pack`, and thus won't contribute to it going forward.",
