            "body": "It seems like a junction link might be able to work on windows. I did have one issue with it though when trying it briefly locally now. I tried to create it through `vim.uv.fs_symlink(path, new_path, { junction = true })`, but I couldn't get it to work with that. I also briefly remember packer.nvim used opt/start, and judging from this commit: https://github.com/wbthomason/packer.nvim/commit/851c62c5ecd3b5adc91665feda8f977e104162a5 I would assume they maybe had it working\n\nIt did however seem to work if I created the link manually in `cmd` with something like this: `mklink /J \"<path>\" \"<new_path>\"`",
