        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I was debating giving it a shot to implement a PR for this, but am unsure about what we would want for some of the actions\n\nThanks for the enthusiasm, but it will probably lead to fewer complications if this waits until there is a lockfie support (#34776, it is in the works and PR should be up *soon*-ish). Mostly because both local plugin and lockfile support will touch a lot of the same areas.\n\nBut to answer the question, the plan is indeed something like you outlined, plus:\n- State of the plugin never changes. Be it in `vim.pack.update()` or during \"install\" / \"checkout\".\n- Confirmation buffer should show a dedicated information about it (that it is local).\n- `vim.pack.get()` should provide specification as for regular plugin, but also will probably introduce a new dedicated `type` field that will be (currently) one of `'git'` or `'local'`.\n\nI have a plan to at least try to resolve this with suggestion PR before 0.12.",
